post.description:
Modify an existing call based on the specified operation:
- OffHook: If idles take the specifed/default address off-hook ready for 'Digits'
- Answer: Answer the specified/default connection (if ringing)
- Drop: Hang-up the connection
- Hold: Put the connection on hold
- Unhold: UnHold the connection
- Transfer: Initiate a consult transfer, send 'Digits' to dial 
- Conference: Initiate a consult conference, send 'Digits' to dial 
- Select: Select a particular Extension/Address and/or Connection before performing operations

Note: Use the select command before performing an operation (i.e. hold, unhold, transfer, conference etc.) the selected address/connection will be used for the next operation(s) on that Phone.

parameters.name: address
parameters.description: The Extension to select (Extension or Line Number, e.g. '1000' or '2')

parameters.name: connection
parameters.description: The Connection instance to modify, for the second conneciton on a line/address use '2'

post.description:
Conference a destination to an existing call, if no number is specified then initiate a consult conference and use the 'Digits' resource to dial the transfer destination.
Note: This requires an exisitng call in the connected state

parameters.name: number
parameters.description: The destination number or SIP Address

parameters.name: address
parameters.description: The Extension to initiate the conference from (Extension or Line Number, e.g. '1000' or '2')

parameters.name: connection
parameters.description: The Connection instance to initiate the conference from, for the second conneciton on a line/address use '2'

post.description:
Send digits to the specified phone, this operation is dependant on the state of the phone:
- No Call: This will initiate on-hook dialing, use the 'Call' operation to dial
- Off-Hook Call: This will use these digits to dial
- Connected Call: This will send these digits as DTMF, you can include commas (',') for 1 second pause i.e. 123,,456

parameters.name: number
parameters.description: The digits to dial or DTMF to send if there is a connected call

Send Raw XML Data to Phone i.e. "<CiscoIPPhoneText>"
